                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>WM. JEFFERSON GUERNSEY&#44; M. D.<lb/>
                1340 FRANKFORD AVE.&#44; PHILADELPHIA.<lb/>
                8 to 9 a. m.&#44; 1 to 8 p. m. &#38; 7 to 8 p. m.<lb/></p>
            
            <p>Rev. S. Morais&#44; L L. D.<lb/>
                546 Nth 5th St<lb/>
                Philada.<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi>. George D. M<hi rend="sup">c</hi>Creary.<lb/>
                Philadelphia.<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>WM. JEFFERSON GUERNSEY&#44; M. D.<lb/>
                1340 FRANKFORD AVE.&#44; PHILADELPHIA.<lb/>
                8 to 9 a. m.&#44; 1 to 8 p. m. &#38; 7 to 8 p. m.<lb/></p>
            <p>July 31st<lb/></p>
            <p>My dear Sir&#58;<lb/></p>
            <p>About a week ago there appeared<lb/> in the Public Ledger an extract<lb/> from some Jewish paper&#44; &#40;probably<lb/> Reformed&#44;&#41;&#45;&#45;I think it was the<lb/> &#34;Exponent&#34;&#45;&#45;stating that there<lb/> was not in any ancient Jewish<lb/> <sic>lithurgy</sic> any prescribed prayers<lb/> for the dead.  Believing that<lb/> this statement is untrue&#44; and as<lb/> a Catholic I am anxious to<lb/> refute it from reliable authority<lb/> among my protestant friends&#44; I take<lb/> the liberty of asking you whether<lb/> such is the case&#63;  Also&#44; whether<lb/> the books of <sic>Machabees</sic> are contained<lb/> in your <sic>authorised</sic> Bible&#63;  Also whether<lb/> prayers <hi rend="underline">to</hi> the dead were allowed&#63;<lb/></p>
            <p>I trust that you will pardon<lb/> this annoyance&#44; but I was anxious<lb/> to appeal to some authority whom<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>I could trust &#38; Dr. Allen who<lb/> married Miss Maggie Cannon&#44; &#40;formerly<lb/> of your neighborhood&#41; has <sic>refered</sic><lb/> me to you<lb/> very respectfully<lb/> Wm. Jefferson Guernsey<lb/></p>
            
            <p>1st. Prayers <hi rend="underline">for</hi> the dead.<lb/>
                2nd Prayers <hi rend="underline">to</hi> the dead<lb/>
                3d Books of <sic>Machabees</sic>.<lb/></p>
            </body>
